usage: git dev [<options>] enter  -- <module-paths>
   or: git dev [<options>] release -- <module-paths>

Manage dev mode.

commands:
    enter                   checkout DEV branches in bundle and specified modules
    release                 merge DEV branches into PROD branches
                                create a PROD branch is necessary (use -v option)
options:
    -h|--help               display help
    -r|--recursive)         visit specified modules recursively
    -v<MAJ.MIN>             specify default version if vbranch does not exist (default to 0.1)
    <module-paths>          specific modules to visit (default to current module)
    
example:
    git dev enter                 # enter DEV mode in bundle and current module
    git dev enter                 # enter DEV mode in bundle and current module
    git dev enter -r              # enter DEV mode in bundle and current module recursively
    git dev enter -- m1 m2        # enter DEV mode in bundle and child modules 'm1' and 'm2'
    git dev release               # release DEV mode in current module
    git dev release -r -- ../m1   # release DEV mode in sibling module 'm1' recursively
    git dev release -v1.0         # release DEV mode in current module
